                            <comment id="12702951" author="jukkaz" created="Sun, 26 Apr 2009 23:40:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Implemented in revision 768819.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can now (optionally) specify a java.uti.concurrent.Executor when creating a ParsingReader instance. This executor is used to execute the background parsing task. The only extra constraint beyond the standard Executor contract is that the executor &lt;b&gt;must&lt;/b&gt; run the task asynchronously in a separate thread.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
